RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 1 7 1/2F Turf CR: 79. Allowance Purse 28000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR MINNESOTA BRED WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this race on the turf, two-year-old races will be run at 6 and 1/2 furlongs and races for three-year-olds and up will be run at a distance of 1 mile on the main track.) (Rail at 30 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DEAR BEAU (IRE) saved ground around the first turn, chased the leaders from the middle of the pack up the backstretch, began a bid from the two path coming around the turn, dueled in upper stretch and pulled clear late. HONEY BELLA saved ground early, dueled on the inside up the backstretch and around the far bend, dug in in upper stretch, was caught with a furlong to go and chased the winner home from there. WILLOWMYGIRL raced off the pace in the two path through the opening half mile, saved ground around the second bend and improved position late. MIZ CALI bumped with the horse to her inside at the start, recovered to duel from the two path around the first turn and up the backstretch, continued to battle around the far turn and tired in the lane. DELUSIONAL DREAM bumped with the horse to her inside leaving the gate and was shuffled back, raced in the two path around the first bend, trailed the field up the backstretch, navigated the far turn still in the two path and made no bid.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 2 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 58. Maiden Claiming Purse 10000. FOR MN-BRED MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SILENT SAILOR stalked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, began a bid from the four path coming around the turn and kicked clear in the lane. MR INSENSITIVE tracked the leader between horses through the opening quarter of a mile, navigated the turn from the four path and chased the winner home in the stretch. BURN BOSS raced off the pace up the backstretch, came around the bend in the three path and gained ground late. RING TAILED TOOTER chased the leader on the inside up the backstretch, raced in the two path around the turn and was outkicked in the stretch. COMO ESTAS dueled on the outside through the early going, continued around the turn in the three path and faded from there. LL'S CLASSY DUDE trailed the field up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and never threatened. POSITIVE PETEY dueled on the inside up the backstretch, saved ground around the bend and tired in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 3 1M Turf CR: 100. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 15000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $8,000 (MINNESOTA BRED $12,500) OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $12,500. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since July 6 All owed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500 (Claiming Races For $10,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances). Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $20,000. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this race on the Turf, it will be run at a distance of 1 Mile on the ma in track.) (Rail at 30 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BIGFOOT CITY led the way while saving ground around the first turn, opened up on the field while racing up the backstretch, came around the far turn in the two path and held off a closer to the wire. CHOCOLATEICECREAM saved ground early, trailed the field well back while racing up the backstretch, navigated the far turn from the three path, launched a bid approaching the quarter pole and gained ground late. ARIES REIGNS bobbled leaving the gate, raced in the two path around the first turn, chased the leader up the backstretch, saved ground around the second bend and kept on in the lane. GOPHER GOLD raced in the middle of the pack on the outside through the opening half mile, came around the far bend in the three path and chased on in the stretch. THICK HAZE saved ground early, settled in the middle of the pack on the inside for the run up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far bend and was outkicked in the lane.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 4 1M Dirt CR: 69. Claiming Purse 10500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR MINNESOTA BRED WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000. Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $7,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PASSTHECAT raced in the three path around the first turn, settled off the pace on the inside for the run up the backstretch, came around the far bend in the four path, began a bid passing the quarter pole and gained ground rapidly on the outside to kick clear. DA GHOST raced in the four path around the first turn, stalked the leaders on the outside up the backstretch, continued around the far turn still in the four path and improved position late. UNIQUE PATH led the field from the three path around the first turn, dueled between horses up the backstretch, continued to battle from the two path around the far turn and weakened late. TIGER HUNTER chased the leader from the two path around the first turn, dueled between horses up the backstretch, continued to battle from the three path around the far bend and weakened late. HARMON KILLER BREW tracked the leaders on the outside through the opening half mile, came around the turn in the three path and faded in the lane. PUBLIC OPINION bumped with the horse to his outside at the start, saved ground around the first turn, chased the leader on the inside up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the second bend and tired in the stretch. WATER TO WINE raced in the five path around the first turn, settled off the pace on the outside for the run up the backstretch, navigated the far turn from the two path and made no bid. THE SWAYZE EXPRESS bumped with the horse to his inside leaving the gate, raced in the two path early, dueled on the inside up the backstretch, dropped back while racing in the two path around the far turn and tired in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 5 5F Dirt CR: 88. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 28000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, TRIAL OR STATE BRED ALLOWANCE OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $16,000. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Si nce July 6 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000. Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $25,000. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this race on the Turf, it will be run at a distance of 5 Furlongs on the main track.) (Rail at 30 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MACHO ROCCO led the way on the inside up the backstretch, dueled from the two path around the bend and dug in gamely in the lane to hold the win. RELEASED tracked the leader on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, came around the turn in the five path, began a bid in upper stretch and dueled to the wire but could not get by the winner. MARVELOUS THUNDER raced in the middle of the pack on the inside early, saved ground around the turn and improved position in the final furlong. TACTICAL ATTACK chased the leader between horses up the backstretch, came around the turn in the four path and weakened in the lane. HAPPY HOUR BOBBY bumped with the horse to his inside at the start, recovered to press the pace between horses up the backstretch, continued around the turn in the three path and faded in the stretch. SHUT UP MICHAEL (IRE) stumbled and bumped with the horse to his outside leaving the gate, trailed the field up the backstretch, raced in the two path around the turn and was empty in the lane.

WINNERS_DETAILS.BREEDER: Libbie Eileen Thiel & Big Dog Racing

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 6 6F Dirt CR: 77. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR MN-BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since July 6 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: EYES FLYING BYE bobbled leaving the gate, recovered to duel on the inside up the backstretch, kicked clear while saving ground around the turn and held that margin to the wire. BURNING LEAVES raced off the pace on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, began a bid from the three path coming around the turn and gained ground late. BIG BOY MCCOY dueled on the outside up the backstretch, raced in the two path around the turn and weakened in the final furlong. ARTIE BELOW ZERO chased the leader on the outside early, navigated the bend from the four path and flattened out in the lane. SMART OXIE raced off the pace on the inside up the backstretch, came around the turn in the two path and never threatened.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 7 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 67. Maiden Special Weight Purse 27000. FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 118 lbs. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this race on the turf, two-year-old races will be run at 6 and 1/2 furlongs and races for three-year-olds and up will be run at a distance of 1 mile on the main track. ) (Rail at 30 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SUPER RENZO stalked the leaders on the outside up the backstretch, began a bid from the three path coming around the turn and dueled gamely to the wire to get the win. CHURCH PEW pressed the pace through the opening quarter of a mile, came around turn in the two path and dueled gamely to the finish to just miss. FORGOT THE ROSES chased the pace setter on the inside up the backstretch, saved ground around the bend and finished evenly. PRINCE IS MY BOY was slow getting into stride, trailing far behind the field up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and made up some ground in the stretch. RIDIN SOLO was sent to an early lead racing up the backstretch, dueled from the two path around the turn and tired in the lane.
